# NOTES for your environments

## Configuration Files

### From Display Manager like XDM

* ~/.profile or ~/.xprofile (the priority below)
* ~/.bashrc is NOT read

### When You Login on Console

* read one of these (with priority)
  1. ~/.bashrc_profile
  2. ~/.bash_login
  3. ~/.profile
* ~/.bashrc is NOT read

### When the bash command is executed

* ~/.bashrc IS read
* ~/.profile, ~/.bash_profile and ~/.bash_login are NOT read
